function execute(address target, bytes calldata data) external {
    require(msg.sender == admin);
    target.call(data);
}

chosen:
**Vulnerability: Unchecked Low-Level Call Return Value (SWC-104)**

`target.call(data)` returns `(bool success, bytes memory returndata)`. If the call reverts or runs out of gas, `success` will be `false`, but the transaction continues silently — the admin does not know the action failed.

**Fix — check the return value:**
```solidity
function execute(address target, bytes calldata data) external {
    require(msg.sender == admin);
    (bool ok, bytes memory ret) = target.call(data);
    require(ok, string(ret));
}
```
Also consider restricting `target` to an approved whitelist to prevent arbitrary external calls.

