// Vulnerable delegatecall
function upgrade(address newImpl) external onlyOwner {
    implementation = newImpl;
}
fallback() external payable {
    (bool ok,) = implementation.delegatecall(msg.data);
    require(ok);
}

chosen:
**Vulnerability: Uninitialized Implementation / Storage Collision**

Two issues:
1. `implementation` could be set to an address with a `selfdestruct` call — one `delegatecall` destroys the proxy.
2. If the new implementation has a different storage layout than the current one, `delegatecall` will corrupt storage slots (variables overwrite each other).

**Fix:**
```solidity
// Use EIP-1967 storage slot to avoid collision
bytes32 private constant IMPL_SLOT =
    bytes32(uint256(keccak256("eip1967.proxy.implementation")) - 1);

function _setImpl(address newImpl) internal {
    require(newImpl.code.length > 0, "not a contract");
    assembly { sstore(IMPL_SLOT, newImpl) }
}
```
Also validate that the new implementation passes a compatibility check (e.g. matches expected interface) before upgrading.

